ntions. While Dolto retains the status of a national treasure, her career has had far-reaching and sometimes harmful repercussions for French society, particularly in the treatment of autism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFamily psychotherapyzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aPsychoanalysiszFrancexHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  aFrançoise Dolto.  aJacques Lacan.  aRené Laforgue.  aautism.  achild psychology.  agender.  ala Maison Verte.  apsychoanalysis.  aradio communication.  asex education.1 aBates, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez978311128144540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615963240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526159632423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526159632/original  a978-3-11-128144-5  Manchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packageb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles